      <div class="document body">
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>The recently created Department for the Use of Muggle Technologies was headed up by Andy Brown. In order to help us understand Muggle Technologies the department created this website so that anyone in the wizarding world with a computer could interact with the Ministry. Although computer uptake is generally low in the wizarding world, the decision was taken to future proof the Ministry and 'bring us into the 21st Century'.</p>

<p>On the 24th of December the Ministry became aware that the website was accessible and viewable by Muggles. Unfortunately the remaining members of the Department for the Use of Muggle Technologies only know how to change content. Experts are being sort out with a greater understanding of the internet and digital.</p>

<h4 id="justice-secretary-chris-grayling-said">Deputy Head of the department, Reg Catermole, said:</h4>

<blockquote>
  <p class="last-child">We are not entirely sure how to shut down the website. We have correctly shut down [the Muggle] government computer, which only required 13 minutes. We then took the extra precaution of destroying the device with a number of spells but that doesn't seem to have done the trick </p>
</blockquote>

<p>It was well documented that the website was run in the cloud. It is not entirely evident which cloud the website is run on, but we currently have teams of ministry officials scouring the skies of Britian searching for this cloud facility. Luckily, we hope to make a discovery fairly soon as we know that <a href="#">clouds in other countries were a serious security risk</a> and so the cloud used for our website is definitely located in the UK.</p>

<h4 id="pm-david-cameron-said">The Minister for Magic said:</h4>

<blockquote>
  <p class="last-child">I am confident that ministry officials will have the matter under control as quickly as magically possible. Until then we urge witches and wizards to be extremely alert and inconspicious in the presence of Muggles. The Ministry thanks you for your support.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Alternative solutions to this issue are being sought. The website was built using the Government Digital Service open source template. We have a highly specialised team of Aurors searching for this source, hoping that they may be able to close it.</p>

<p>We are also seeking input from large government IT suppliers, although the recently departed Head of Muggle Technology insisted we have nothing to do with them, they have assured us they provide Value For Gold (VFG) on all large scale government IT projects and they always deliver on time and budget.</p>

</div>
